reviews.text: This small quaint Japanese restaurant only seats 10 but is hands down one of these best omakase sushi restaurants in town.  I'd recommend you to watch 'Jiro Dreams of Sushi' before coming here as you will have a deeper understanding and respect for the food.  One star less than 5 because the octopus is no longer included in the set but is an extra charge.  For the amount of money, they should include it again. Tip: eat the sushi with your hands and not with chopsticks; it enhances the authentic experience.  Also, stick to lunch as it's better value than dinner I reckon.

A three star Michelin restaurant serving Japanese Omakase tasting menu. Open for lunch and dinner. The only three star Michelin restaurant in Hong Kong serving Omakase set meal. Native Japanese chef with most ingredients freshly flown direct from Japan.
the absolute best meal of my life. top notch ingredients simply prepared to great effect. phenomenal food made by a master.

Can understand why a 3* Michelin can be 50% full for a 2nd seating... 

Came here for a friends special bday and made bookings in advance. Friend arrived at 8:15 but was told the table wasn’t ready until 8:30. At 8:30 we asked again and they said 1 more minute but then they sat us down around 8:40, after the guests left and they cleaned up. Head chef greets guests at the door as they leave to hand out business cards.

Lucky for me I had good company otherwise it’d be a tough dinner to sit through. 

Food was great! Abalone signature was top in terms of flavour, tenderness and freshness. Baby snapper was really delicate and refreshing. Two types of sea urchin was also a hit as the uni was really fresh. 

The red vinegar traditional rice is good but also a bit pungent and takes away from the seafood flavour. Didn’t have to add any sauce but you will find your mouth lined with a vinaigrette tang. 

Otoro had tendon so literally impossible to melt in your mouth. We wanted to order a 720 ML sake and asked for advise but all we got was it’s dry / sweet or should be drank cold best. No depth to the origin of the sake, or any key unique features and for any bottles of sake prices 1,200 -15,000 you would really expect a bit more. At least a suggestion on why this sake goes well with the omakase. 

So why 1*? I’m not a food critic and I’m not a chef so my opinions are solely based on my personal taste and preference of what I would expect from a 3* institution. 

Key observations / feeling: 
- Two local servers were friendliest throughout the night but were also hard sellers:
- always resorted to the higher priced menu items without even asking for preference / background 
- asked if you wanted to add more food without asking if you were full 
- language , spoke in Cantonese and described every dish to us , assume if you didn’t speak their language it would have been English instead 
- Head chef didn’t introduce himself at all nor did he have any interest to engage with his customers ( our party of 2 nor the party of 2 beside us) 
- for an Omakase with 5 applies and 8 pieces of sushi, we had to wolf it all down in 70 mins 
- we gave feedback to the server that food was too rushed and rather than taking accountability, she said: “it’s because there’s only 4 customers today so the serving time is quicker “ ... my friend even said: shouldn’t you guys have food timing figured out in advance , especially when you knew we would be four ppl... 
- had to ask for them to hold off desert as we still had 360mL of our sake left... and that we could digest our food a bit 

Drum roll Dealbreaker: 
At least 10:35 we (my friend and I and the party of 2 beside us) were asked by the Head chef-San that they were about to close... and that he hinted we should leave. 0 reminders or mentioning of closing time or seating limit especially when we were sat in later. We still had 2 final glasses of sake to finish so quickly drank it the 4 of us took the hint and left. Head chef did a quick greet by the door but surprise : no business cards and no dialogue. 

If you need to check off a 3* Michelin off your bucket list, best to put this last on your list. 

Didn’t take photos as we were there for the experience and not the show.

Customer will become loyal customer after the 7th visit. Shikon failed us at 4th time. A Michelin 3 star sushi restaurant gave us the following experience last night

- we booked 6pm, and they told us the fish arrival late that day so we’d start the meal at 6:20pm
- we got fish scale, bone, and dish washing iron wire in our meal (3 out of 6 got fish bone in meal)
- and the chef told us that having fish bone in the sardines sushi is normal...Is it? I am not sure

I am not sure if I’d come back again for such a high price Michelin 3 star sushi restaurant...

reviews.text: I have stayed at this hotel with family twice now . Ir is by far the best hotel  we have stated in ever. The service is top notch . They  think  of everything to make your stay more comfortable . From fruit bowl and fresh pastries  face masks, foot spray all sorts of little touches which we appreciate. The spa is one of the best in any hotel. We had massages and facials all top quality . We will continue to be repeat clients in this hotel.

We stayed in this establishment 4 months ago with family. The hotel is expensive, but to compare the hotels we have stayed since (8+) The Landmark is still the best hotel we have been in. The service from walking in the front door is spot on. Its not just service with a smile, it's the genuine nature of all the staff who assisted us proactively.    Waylon and staff service A++ (any parent would be proud with an A+ :P) you guys/gals are unreal. not sure if its the training you were given, or just the experiences you have developed over years. I couldn't fault it. Rooms and Food is massive tick. Location of the hotel is perfect. shop,food,party,transport all within 100m walking distance. Hope to see the same crew when I return one day.

K & N

A sumptuous 5 star hotel. We just had lunch here and the cuisine was impressive. We cannot comment on the rooms as we didn't stay here. The food was exquisite and delicious. The price we finally paid was bewildering.

5 stars hotel indeed! the staffs here are super friendly and supreme service! the room is nice. the location is perfect for all kind of tourists or business men. 24hrs in-room dining and service. i would say it’s one of the best hotel that i have stayed. i would love to stay here again. kudos to all staffs here.
Upscale swanky hotel connected to a large mall. Neila went above and beyond in helping me get to know the area and provided some super helpful tips.

reviews.text: 三星餐廳，果然不同凡響。細節上，醋飯和薑的味道具有一致性相當難得；菜餚中，軟絲壽司絲滑順口不會太黏、煮章魚恰到好處的口感、中鮪大腹特有的香氣、招牌鮑魚肝醬拌飯沒有一絲腥味、虎蝦壽司極甜、星鰻壽司入口即化，是場美妙的味覺饗宴，加上柿沼師傅細心的解說與親切的笑容，米其林三星當之無愧。

三星原來這麼厲害。
本來只是陪客去吃名氣，同行友人吃到流淚，感動阿。
主廚很親切，還會用國語和我們打招呼，最後還親自到店外送我們離開。
能夠享用這麼美味的料理，應該是我們謝謝主廚。
另外，2019年5月2日，志魂會搬遷到東方文華酒店。

reviews.text: One of the famous shopping malls in Hong Kong. It is very spacious shopping mall spread across multiple floors. You will find many international brands shops here. Easy to reach via Central MTR station. Good meeting place. There are good number of restaurants also.

This is a very elegant and exclusive restaurant which serves beautifully prepared local food and the service is outstanding. Both the food and the drinks were of high quality. The waiter was attentive, friendly and helpful when going through the menu. His recommendations were excellent and according to what we desired. The price level is rather high, but you pay for what you get. 

Please press the like button :)

Large and very spacious shopping mall spread out over multiple floors. Primarily focusing on luxury shopping brands and non-chain snacks and food, visiting here and spending money can be for rather nice special occasions. Directly connected to the Central station MTR exits, and also the centre of walkways to multiple other malls in Central, this is a place with a lot of foot traffic though, so make sure you go with the flow if you're just passing through. Signage can be very confusing though, so you might need to walk around to find where you need to go.

Landmark is a famous shopping mall located in Central. Its upper floors are all office, while the lower floors are restaurants and famous shops. Here you can see a lot of luxury items such as designer handbags, fashions and jewelry. These items are very expensive and cannot be afforded by ordinary people.
Most renown brands are in this place, and it has a lots of cafe area. Center piece display at the water fountain is also something local tourist love to visit.
